I wish for the same thing.

532
01:00:34,409 --> 01:00:37,809
But we're the only ones

533
01:00:37,809 --> 01:00:39,970
who can help him.

534
01:01:30,964 --> 01:01:32,837
I'll take that.

535
01:01:56,336 --> 01:02:00,069
- Hello! 
 - Hi, Eun Yeong.

536
01:02:00,975 --> 01:02:02,789
Can I please have two gimbaps? 
  (T/N: Seaweed rice rolls with vegetables, seafood, and meat)

537
01:02:02,789 --> 01:02:04,915
Okay. Just a minute.

538
01:02:04,922 --> 01:02:08,649
How are things going with moving?

539
01:02:08,689 --> 01:02:09,896
Not good.

540
01:02:09,896 --> 01:02:12,689
We're still waiting for the compensation.

541
01:02:12,716 --> 01:02:16,575
Everybody's suffering, I guess.

542
01:02:29,917 --> 01:02:31,837
I just cooked these.

543
01:02:31,884 --> 01:02:35,150
- Bring these home. 
 - They're too small.

544
01:02:35,150 --> 01:02:38,064
Don't worry. You don't have to pay for these.

545
01:02:38,090 --> 01:02:40,797
- Thank you. 
 - Sure.

546
01:02:40,797 --> 01:02:43,603
- I'll see you around. 
 - See you.

547
01:02:43,663 --> 01:02:46,197
Take care.

548
01:02:56,452 --> 01:03:01,038
I heard Yong Seob's having his third trial.

549
01:03:02,305 --> 01:03:03,966
Yes.

550
01:03:06,452 --> 01:03:09,845
Don't stress over giving a testimony.

551
01:03:09,925 --> 01:03:13,018
I'm sure you'll do fine.

552
01:03:15,703 --> 01:03:19,216
You've pulled through, so I know you can do this.

553
01:03:46,877 --> 01:03:50,243
I'd like to welcome you all

554
01:03:50,243 --> 01:03:53,570
to our new party house.

555
01:03:53,570 --> 01:03:56,490
- How are you, Congressman? 
 - Oh.

556
01:03:56,490 --> 01:03:58,203
Sir!

557
01:03:58,203 --> 01:04:00,040
Welcome, Professor.

558
01:04:00,992 --> 01:04:02,124
The night is young,

559
01:04:02,124 --> 01:04:06,806
so let's get started and blow our stress away!

560
01:04:07,929 --> 01:04:09,495
Sir!

561
01:04:10,148 --> 01:04:11,993
Welcome.

562
01:04:13,837 --> 01:04:15,360
Good.

563
01:04:16,031 --> 01:04:18,933
Give me just two minutes.

564
01:04:23,436 --> 01:04:26,147
Hey, where are you?

565
01:04:26,147 --> 01:04:30,020
I'm dropping by the office for a bit. It won't take long.

566
01:04:30,020 --> 01:04:31,952
I'll be there soon.

567
01:04:31,952 --> 01:04:33,527
Okay.

568
01:04:53,740 --> 01:04:55,960

569
01:05:22,063 --> 01:05:24,617
Do you work for the demolition company?

570
01:05:24,617 --> 01:05:26,025
What is it?

571
01:05:26,025 --> 01:05:30,804
Hello. My name is Do Eun Yeong, and I'm a resident of Area 5.

572
01:05:30,804 --> 01:05:33,634
I need your help with some tenancy issues.

573
01:05:33,634 --> 01:05:37,270
I can't help you. I'm not the boss here.

574
01:05:38,259 --> 01:05:43,575
Could you delay the demolition until we've gotten our compensation?

575
01:05:47,204 --> 01:05:48,711
Well, then,

576
01:05:49,397 --> 01:05:51,351
go wait in the car.

577
01:05:51,351 --> 01:05:55,694
I'll take you to my boss when I'm done here.

578
01:05:55,694 --> 01:05:57,457
Okay?

579
01:05:57,457 --> 01:05:59,231
Thank you.

580
01:06:23,095 --> 01:06:24,861
Don't do this.

581
01:06:24,861 --> 01:06:28,790
It won't help to ask them. Don't go.

582
01:06:44,420 --> 01:06:46,164
Hey.

583
01:06:46,164 --> 01:06:48,510
I'm out for a bit.

584
01:06:49,248 --> 01:06:52,868
The key? It should be there.

585
01:06:54,320 --> 01:06:57,468
Okay. I'm on my way.

586
01:07:31,263 --> 01:07:33,960
What? Where's that girl?

587
01:08:08,990 --> 01:08:11,460
- See you tomorrow. 
 - Okay.

588
01:08:11,460 --> 01:08:13,930
See you guys.

589
01:08:18,258 --> 01:08:20,617
How are you?

590
01:08:20,617 --> 01:08:22,930
I'm well. Thanks.

591
01:08:22,930 --> 01:08:25,625
I won't have any problem working.

592
01:08:25,625 --> 01:08:29,117
You're always so hard at work.

593
01:08:29,117 --> 01:08:32,782
You would always come in early and go home late.

594
01:08:33,734 --> 01:08:35,895
This might be tough for you.

595
01:08:35,895 --> 01:08:38,841
I understand you because I'm a friend.

596
01:08:38,841 --> 01:08:42,013
But the students' parents are different.

597
01:08:42,013 --> 01:08:46,838
There are a few that are not happy about you joining us.

598
01:08:47,779 --> 01:08:49,800
Will you be okay?

599
01:08:50,567 --> 01:08:52,482
Of course.

600
01:08:52,482 --> 01:08:54,793
Thank you for the opportunity.

601
01:09:32,462 --> 01:09:35,079

602
01:10:11,634 --> 01:10:16,059

603
01:11:04,715 --> 01:11:08,546
Why did you say that yesterday?

604
01:11:11,122 --> 01:11:14,140
That it wouldn't help to ask.

605
01:11:15,704 --> 01:11:19,746
I kept thinking about it.

606
01:11:22,610 --> 01:11:24,566
I'm sorry.

607
01:11:25,128 --> 01:11:27,826
That was all I could say.

608
01:11:29,401 --> 01:11:33,066
I was upset that a stranger found out

609
01:11:33,066 --> 01:11:35,709
about what I'm going through.

610
01:11:37,476 --> 01:11:41,620
I'm sorry I pretended to know.

611
01:11:45,126 --> 01:11:49,810
I was scared that I might repeat the same mistake from the past.

612
01:11:51,819 --> 01:11:54,308
I couldn't help it.

613
01:12:00,336 --> 01:12:02,910
I also felt thankful.

614
01:12:07,544 --> 01:12:09,932
It put my heart at ease.

615
01:12:12,556 --> 01:12:15,857
I used to think it was all my fault

616
01:12:15,857 --> 01:12:19,170
that I have to go through this misery.

617
01:12:19,170 --> 01:12:22,795
That made me anxious.

618
01:12:22,795 --> 01:12:26,991
When you told me that, I felt hopeless for a second.

619
01:12:28,130 --> 01:12:30,670
But now I know it's not my fault.

620
01:12:30,670 --> 01:12:32,463
So that felt good.

621
01:12:45,764 --> 01:12:48,956
I wonder what happened to the people that lived here.

622
01:12:49,741 --> 01:12:52,475
I wonder how they are now.

623
01:12:52,475 --> 01:12:54,345
I'm curious to know.

624
01:12:56,602 --> 01:12:59,338
Life must have been tough for them.

625
01:13:01,423 --> 01:13:03,118
Still,

626
01:13:04,290 --> 01:13:07,552
they won't live in poverty forever.

627
01:13:11,586 --> 01:13:13,916
Things will change, right?

628
01:13:19,459 --> 01:13:21,582
They should.

629
01:13:23,092 --> 01:13:25,012
They will.

